What you need to know:  Cash-strapped Spire Bank, which was recently acquired by Equity Bank, has been ordered to preserve more than Sh41 million held in an account at Waiyaki Way branch in Nairobi following the death of an advocate.The money, which is proceeds of a court award, belongs to at least 43 former employees of Nairobi Water and Sewerage Company.High Court judge Maureen Odero directed that no withdrawals should be made from the account until further orders are issued by the court.